name: Clifton Park Orchard
short_description: Heritage fruit trees in the town's premier park.
description: The Walled Garden and surrounding areas contain established apple and pear trees available for public picking.

name: Thrybergh Country Park Hazelnuts
description: Hazel and sweet chestnut trees are found along the 2nd half of the reservoir circular walk.

name: Greasbrough Canal Wild Garlic
short_description: Pungent spring greens by the water.
description: Shaded sections of the canal path heading toward Wentworth are rich with wild garlic in April.

name: Incredible Edible Rotherham - Minster
description: Community raised beds featuring kale, chives, and seasonal kitchen herbs.

name: Wath-upon-Dearne Blackberries
short_description: Bramble thickets on old railway lines.
description: The Trans-Pennine Trail sections through Wath offer extensive blackberry picking.

name: Ulley Country Park Elder
description: Large elder bushes are scattered throughout the parkland and around the reservoir.

name: Wentworth Estate Chestnuts
description: Mature sweet chestnuts found on public footpaths surrounding the Wentworth Woodhouse estate.

name: Wickersley Woods Bluebells & Sorrel
description: Lemon-flavoured wood sorrel can be found in the dappled shade of this ancient woodland.

name: Rother Valley Country Park Rosehips
description: Numerous wild rose bushes providing rosehips line the trails around the main lake.

name: Brinsworth Incredible Edible Planters
description: Street-side beds with accessible strawberries and culinary herbs for locals.

name: Maltby Crags Sloes
description: Sloe berries can be gathered from the dense blackthorn scrub on the limestone crags.

name: Grange Park Orchard
description: A small stand of apple and plum trees planted for community use.

name: Trans-Pennine Trail Samphire (Inland Alternative)
description: Wild celery and watermint found in the damp drainage dykes along the trail.

name: Silverwood Forest Haws
description: The newly planted woodland areas at the old pit site are rich in hawthorn berries.

name: Moorgate Walnuts
description: Mature walnut trees overhang public pavements in this established leafy suburb.
